description: A platform developed from an open framework to help AI researchers and developers to rapidly prototype, test and deploy workflows that include machine learning models as worker components. The workflow can be invoked on command line or web service, as well as integrated into UX/UI as part of a larger intelligent solution.

A comprehensive AI project featuring machine learning model training, AI agent implementation using Microsoft Agent Framework, REST API, React UI, and Azure Development Kit evaluation with Docker deployment.

A framework for evaluating explainable AI (XAI) methods in drug discovery using multiple machine learning architectures. This repository implements three distinct model architectures (CNN, Random Forest, and RGCN) and provides a hierarchical four-tier evaluation framework for assessing the quality and reliability of their explanations.

This repository contains the full-stack code for a serverless, real-time water quality monitoring system. An ESP32 microcontroller sends sensor data (pH, turbidity, etc.) to a serverless backend on AWS, which processes the data, runs a machine learning model, stores it in DynamoDB. A dynamic web frontend then visualizes this data on a Leaflet map.

This project is an **advanced multi-stage Bitcoin ECDSA signature analyzer and recovery system**.   It integrates **machine learning (XGBoost, LSTM, GAN)**, **reinforcement learning (Gym)**, and **genetic algorithms**   to automatically detect weak or reused nonces across blockchain transactions and attempt secure key reconstruction.

A machine learning framework using Logistic Regression, Random Forest, and XGBoost to detect credit card fraud in real time. Built on the Kaggle dataset, it delivers scalable, explainable, and business-ready risk scoring for banks and financial institutions.

Petastorm library enables single machine or distributed training and evaluation of deep learning models from datasets in Apache Parquet format. It supports ML frameworks such as Tensorflow, Pytorch, and PySpark and can be used from pure Python code.

Flask is a lightweight, open-source Python web framework used in Data Science to deploy and manage data-driven applications. It offers a simple yet powerful structure for creating web apps and APIs that integrate with data analysis or machine learning models, providing flexibility for custom solutions.

This project examines how machines can learn from human fallibility, model disagreement, and align with moral reasoning. It blends psychology, fairness metrics, interpretability, and co-learning design into one framework for humane intelligence.

TensorFlow is an open-source machine learning framework developed by Google. It provides strong support for various platforms, especially Linux, and is widely adopted in the industry due to its active community and production-ready capabilities.

AI-VAPT is an autonomous, AI-driven Vulnerability Assessment & Penetration Testing (VAPT) framework designed to revolutionize cybersecurity testing. The platform combines traditional manual VAPT methodologies with neural intelligence, machine learning, and intelligent automation. It supports continuous, scalable, and context-aware vulnerability.

This project is a complete, end-to-end machine learning workflow to predict passenger survival from the famous Titanic dataset. The primary goal was to build a reliable classifier while mastering a repeatable framework for data cleaning, feature engineering, and model training.

This project focuses on developing an optimized multi-model fusion approach to enhance the accuracy of lung cancer prediction using machine learning and deep learning techniques. By combining multiple models and optimizing their performance, the system aims to provide a more reliable and robust prediction framework for early lung cancer detection.
